fields.physical_description: Design: printed card, numbered, each with an illustration and caption and in one corner a small version of a playing card from the 4 suits; unnumbered title card; colour lithographs
fields.title: la sibylle des salons
fields.history_note: This set is probably a reissue of LA JEU DE LA SYBELLE DES SALONS by Gaudais, issued in 1830 and consisting of hand coloured lithographs, see C P Hargrave A History of Playing Cards, Boston & New York, 1930, p.76,79
fields.production_note: published by B-P Grimaud, 54 Rue de Lancy Paris; P Oberthur, Rennes (858-20) -lettered on rules booklet
fields.historical_context_note:
